  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.13.0\n\n### What happened?\n\nSetting the gas price does not have any observable effect, either during tests or running the node.\r\n\r\nConnecting to the provider and using `ethers` 's `getGasPrice` returns:\r\n\r\n- 8 gwei for berlin hardforks\r\n- 1.8 gwei if the hardfork is left unspecified\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\nRun a hardhat instance with the following config:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport { HardhatUserConfig } from \"hardhat/config\";\r\nimport \"@nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox\";\r\nimport { utils } from \"ethers\";\r\n\r\nconst gasPrice = utils.parseUnits(\"900\", \"gwei\").toNumber();\r\n\r\nconst config: HardhatUserConfig = {\r\n  solidity: \"0.8.18\",\r\n  networks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      // hardfork: 'berlin',\r\n      gasPrice,\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n};\r\n\r\nexport default config;\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen use, either in tests or connecting via an external script to the node (`npx hardhat node`) \r\n\r\n```ts\r\nprovider\r\n        .getGasPrice()\r\n        .then((price) => console.log(\"PRICE\", price.toString()));\r\n``` \n\n### Search terms\n\ngasPrice, gas, price, config",
